subSubSection.paragraph:
M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 and 2 and mesotarsomeres 1 distinctly widened, narrower than apices of respective tibiae. Aedeagus (
Figs 148, 149
) 0.85 mm long, symmetrical. Apical process of median lobe much shorter than basal bulb, hardly inflexed, with ventral branch narrowed apically and truncate at tip. Parameres not lobed, gradually narrowed apically, bent in apical fourth and overlapping. Internal sac lacking sclerotized pieces, with long spines in apical section, very fine denticular and scale-like structures in large middle section, larger denticles in proximal part.
